The king weakfish, Macrodon ancylodon ...  abundance and its wide consumer acceptance (Cervign 1993; Haimovici et al. 1996; Isaac & Braga 1999).The bottom-feeding  M. ancylodon  is distributed in a wide
geographical area along the Atlantic coast of South America. It is found from the Gulf of Paria in Venezuela to Bahia Blanca in Argentina. The distribution ranges from 10 N to 40 , and approximately 10 000 km of coastline (Fig. 1). 
This species has restricted migratory habit and inhabits coastal and estuarine areas (Yamaguti 1979). It spawns near river deltas since estuary areas are used as nursery grounds and areas where juveniles remain until the beginning of sexual maturity (Yamaguti 1979; Camargo-Zorro 1999)
